biography.value: A werewolf is a savage predator that can appear as a humanoid, as a wolf, or in a terrifying hybrid form—a furred and well-muscled humanoid body topped by a ravening wolf’s head.

description.value:
(&Reference[humanoid]{Humanoid} or Hybrid Form Only). The werewolf makes two attacks: two with its spear (&Reference[humanoid]{humanoid} form) or one with its bite and one with its claws (hybrid form).

The [[lookup @name]] uses [[lookup @item.name]].

Melee Weapon Attack: +4 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: [[/damage 1d8 + @mod type=piercing average=true]] damage. If the target is a &Reference[humanoid]{humanoid}, it must succeed on a [[/save con 12 format=long]] or be cursed with werewolf lycanthropy.

The [[lookup @name]] attacks with its [[lookup @item.name]].

(Hybrid Form Only). Melee Weapon Attack: +4 to hit, reach 5 ft., one creature. Hit: [[/damage 2d4 + @mod type=slashing average=true]] damage.

The [[lookup @name]] attacks with its [[lookup @item.name]].

Melee or Ranged Weapon Attack: +4 to hit, reach 5 ft. or range 20/60 ft., one creature. Hit: [[/damage 1d6 + @mod type=piercing average=true]] damage, or [[/damage 1d8 + @mod type=piercing average=true]] damage if used with two hands to make a melee attack.

The [[lookup @name]] attacks with its [[lookup @item.name]].

Shapechanger. The werewolf can use its action to polymorph into a wolf-humanoid hybrid or into a wolf, or back into its true form, which is &Reference[humanoid]{humanoid}. Its statistics, other than its AC, are the same in each form. Any equipment it is wearing or carrying isn't transformed. It reverts to its true form if it dies.

The [[lookup @name]] uses [[lookup @item.name]].

Keen Hearing and Smell. The werewolf has advantage on &Reference[wis]{Wisdom} (&Reference[prc]{Perception}) checks that rely on hearing or smell.
